<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
[[ Genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25612A22-875C-4BA3-BDA3-8737B7CAD349" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microsynodontis Boulenger</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
The genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25612A22-875C-4BA3-BDA3-8737B7CAD349" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microsynodontis</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the rivers of western Africa (from the Saint Paul River drainage south and east to the Congo River drainage), and is comprised of small mochokid catfishes diagnosed by the following synapomorphies: a narrow mesethmoid, lack of free orbital margin, transverse ventral fold of branchiostegal membranes, slender cleithral process, and a rounded or truncate caudal fin (Howes, 1980).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
Currently, there are four nominal species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25612A22-875C-4BA3-BDA3-8737B7CAD349" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microsynodontis</taxonomicName>
, viz. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DBDC9D70-13DA-4626-9564-2CF145D5001A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis batesii Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="batesii">M. batesii Boulenger, 1903</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3D4D06C3-7DA0-4BE6-B2B5-D09FCE764FCE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis christyi Boulenger 1920:32" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="christyi">M. christyi Boulenger, 1920</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5BE69781-9A57-48A5-B5D4-0536CFF434F6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis lamberti Poll &amp; Gosse 1963:61" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lamberti">M. lamberti Poll &amp; Gosse, 1963</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:01EB9BD8-DCC9-4A12-B636-A4C4A93C8B2F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis polli Lambert 1958:42" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="polli">M. polli Lambert, 1958</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3D4D06C3-7DA0-4BE6-B2B5-D09FCE764FCE" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis christyi Boulenger 1920:32" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="christyi">Microsynodontis christyi</taxonomicName>
has been considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DBDC9D70-13DA-4626-9564-2CF145D5001A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis batesii Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="batesii">M. batesii</taxonomicName>
(fide Matthes, 1964), but is a valid species. The freshwater ichthyofauna of the lower Guinea region (here defined as the portion of west central Africa delineated by the Cross River drainage to the north and the Chiloango River drainage to the south; fide Roberts, 1975) is one of the least explored in Africa (Teugels &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="GuÃ©gan">Guegan</normalizedToken>
, 1994). 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DBDC9D70-13DA-4626-9564-2CF145D5001A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis batesii Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="batesii">Microsynodontis batesii</taxonomicName>
is the only species known from there.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="2">
While preparing an account of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25612A22-875C-4BA3-BDA3-8737B7CAD349" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microsynodontis</taxonomicName>
for a forthcoming publication on the fishes of the lower Guinea region (Ng, in prep.), it was found that material from the region previously identified as 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:DBDC9D70-13DA-4626-9564-2CF145D5001A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis batesii Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="batesii">M. batesii</taxonomicName>
consisted of nine distinct species, eight of which are undescribed. This study reviews the 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25612A22-875C-4BA3-BDA3-8737B7CAD349" class="Actinopterygii" family="Mochokidae" genus="Microsynodontis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microsynodontis Boulenger 1903:26" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microsynodontis</taxonomicName>
of the lower Guinea region, with the eight new species described herein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
